<h3>Biography</h3>
<p>Katlynn Oliver is an associate attorney who assists clients with estate planning, estate administration, real estate transactions, and business matters. Before becoming a lawyer, she gained valuable experience in corporate media and real estate drafting, which gives her a unique perspective and sharp eye for detail. Katlynn graduated from Duquesne University with a bachelor's degree in Public Relations and Advertising and a minor in Business.</p>
<p>She went on to earn her law degree from the Duquesne University Kline School of Law, after which she completed 425 hours of pro bono work, earning the Pro Bono Exemplary Service Certification. She is licensed to practice law in Pennsylvania state courts and the federal courts in the Western District of Pennsylvania, and she is also a licensed Pennsylvania Notary.</p>
<p>Katlynn lives in Washington Township with her husband and their two dogs. Outside of work, she enjoys staying active by boxing, kayaking, and exploring the outdoors. She is passionate about helping families plan for the future and ensuring their legal affairs are in order for the long term.</p>
